result.execSummary:
The defendant Jay John Koechell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent with: Waushara Co Case No. 2015CF000118

miscConds.notes: Costs paid in full from cash bond previously posted.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars (restaurant area of a bar or tavern would not be considered a violation), and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  Any possession of prescribed medications must also be in the proper quantity prescribed.
Defendant is ordered to participate and successfully complete the Waushara County TAD/Safe Streets Program.    DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.
